ens.<\/p>\n","question_id":2881,"tags":["lab-techniques","sds-page","imaging","green-fluorescent-protein"],"score":7,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":601,"up_vote_count":7},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d5e8817011bf40f20c518af3c0dc7187?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":137,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/137/kennypeanuts","reputation":1522,"display_name":"KennyPeanuts","accept_rate":75},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ef067cf09ffd3cc8f069bacec73c8202?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":222,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/222/david-lebauer","reputation":780,"display_name":"David LeBauer","accept_rate":80},"score":0,"post_id":2455,"edited":false,"creation_date":1339731130,"comment_id":3677,"body":"I&#39;d be curious to know if the book I suggested (Methods in Ecosystem Science) meets your needs, or if you find an alternative."}],"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ef067cf09ffd3cc8f069bacec73c8202?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":222,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/222/david-lebauer","reputation":780,"display_name":"David LeBauer","accept_rate":80},"score":3,"is_accepted":true,"down_vote_count":0,"last_activity_date":1338617852,"creation_date":1338617852,"body":"<p><a href=\"http://books.google.com/books/about/Methods_in_Ecosystem_Science.html?id=N_pGrSntap0C\" rel=\"nofollow\">Methods in Ecosystem Science<\/a> edited by Oswaldo Sala, Rob Jackson, Hal Mooney, and Robert Howarth is a classic standard reference used by many (most?) ecosystem ecologists.<\/p>\n","answer_id":2470,"question_id":2455,"up_vote_count":3},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f50c9bbddddd104fb95d3839ef0fb1dd?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":1396,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1396/rioraider","repu