periencing auditory hallucinations. A study conducted by the La Trobe University School of Psychological Sciences revealed that as few as five cups of coffee a day could trigger the phenomenon.<\/li>\n<li>High caffeine consumption accelerates bone loss at the spine in elderly postmenopausal women.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<p>The list above comes from the very comprehensive wikipedia page on the health effects of caffeine. In fact, wikipedia is particularly good on this subject, see the following pages:<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caffeine\">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caffeine<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Health_effects_of_caffeinehttp://\">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Health_effects_of_caffeine<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Health_effects_of_coffee\">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Health_effects_of_coffee<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p><sup>1<\/sup> Our bodies <em>do<\/em> produce both Oxygen and water as byproducts of various reactions but nowhere near enough to satisfy our need for these substances. <\/p>\n","answer_id":3893,"question_id":3892,"up_vote_count":11,"last_edit_date":1349976540}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/3892/does-drinking-coffee-have-negative-effects","last_activity_date":1349976540,"creation_date":1349948044,"answer_count":1,"title":"Does drinking coffee have negative effects?","body":"<p>From what I collected, coffee is a magical potion that lets you feel energetic, and essentially not-sleepy. But are there any tradeoffs? I mean, if it was so beneficial, wouldn't the human body produce caffeine naturally?<\/p>\n","question_id":3892,"tags":["biochemistry"],"score":8,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":909,"up_vote_count":8},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b935a7d95c904243e5bc325587927fe9?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":1523,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1523/bob-kaufman","reputation":133,"d