hat the two are chemically bonded together, but that is incorrect. What actually happens is that the compound is an ionic salt, in the form [compound]H<sup>+<\/sup> Cl<sup>-<\/sup>. As far as absorption, that is entirely dependent on the compound(s) being absorbed. Once you swallow them, they dissociate back into the weak acid form and H<sup>+<\/sup>,Cl<sup>-<\/sup> ions.<\/p>\n","answer_id":3842,"question_id":3839,"up_vote_count":8}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/3839/where-are-hcl-supplements-absorbed-in-the-human-digestive-system","last_activity_date":1349715316,"creation_date":1349624263,"answer_count":1,"title":"Where are -HCl supplements absorbed in the human digestive system?","body":"<p>I see that quite a lot of drugs and dietary supplements sold in the USA have -HCl(hydrochloride) added to their name. For example pyridoxine hydrochloride for Vitamin B6.  <strong>I'm interested in knowing where in the digestive system -HCl compounds are absorbed?<\/strong> Is it in the stomach? <\/p>\n\n<p>It would also help if I get a rough idea of how long it takes for -HCl supplements to be absorbed. Is it an hour or more?<\/p>\n\n<p>Thank you for your input! <\/p>\n","question_id":3839,"tags":["human-biology","digestive-system"],"score":3,"accepted_answer_id":3842,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":136,"up_vote_count":3,"last_edit_date":1349715316},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/Ya95U.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":1474,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1474/matthew-higgins","reputation":288,"display_name":"Matthew Higgins","accept_rate":100},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/66c66c4d97a7bc3859a85253f003e1fb?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"moderator","user_id":6,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6/mad-scientist","reputation":6781,"display_name":"Mad Scientist","accept_rate":55},"score":1,"post_id":3847,"edited":false,"creation