ody":"<p>Darwin had written lots of papers which dealt with <em>fertilization<\/em> (which involves single cells), as he primarily dealt with the reproduction, continuation and thus evolution of a species, but these did not deal with cell biology specifically.<\/p>\n\n<p>After a closer look at the <a href=\"http://darwin-online.org.uk/contents.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">complete list of all his publications<\/a>, I found that he did have two cell-related publishings, specifically about <strong>the size of cells<\/strong>, one entitled <a href=\"http://darwin-online.org.uk/converted/pdf/1862_jamaica_F1826_001.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bees in Jamaica increase the size and substance of their cells<\/a>, and the other, <a href=\"http://darwin-online.org.uk/converted/pdf/1862_beecells_F1824_001.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bee-cells in Jamaica not larger than in England<\/a>, in which he retracts the statement he had made in the previous article.  <\/p>\n\n<p>Ultimately, to answer your question, it seems as though none of his works dealt with <em>cellular structures<\/em>.<\/p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<h2>References<\/h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p><strong>Charles Darwin<\/strong>. <em>\"Bees in Jamaica increase the size and substance of their cells\".<\/em> Journal of Horticulture (15 July): 305.<\/p><\/li>\n<li><p><strong>Charles Darwin<\/strong>. <em>\"Bee-cells in Jamaica not larger than in England.\"<\/em> Journal of Horticulture (22 July): 323.<\/p><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n","answer_id":3782,"question_id":3781,"up_vote_count":2}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/3781/what-is-the-title-of-darwins-paper-on-cellular-structure","last_activity_date":1349347799,"creation_date":1349302039,"answer_count":1,"title":"What is the title of Darwin's paper on cellular structure?","body":"<p>I read somewhere that Darwin wrote a paper that dealt with cellular structure, but I've been unable to find the title or contents of the paper because Darwin wrote such a volume of material. What is the title of this 