me.<\/p>\n\n<p>So my question is, is the <strong>volume<\/strong> of an adipocyte cell always directly proportional to the <strong>weight<\/strong> of the fat stored within the cell?   <\/p>\n\n<p>If not, what factors would increase/decrease the size of the adipocyte cell for a given mass of stored fat?<\/p>\n","question_id":3739,"tags":["human-biology"],"score":9,"accepted_answer_id":3779,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":148,"up_vote_count":9},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/7974275b33c1c13d775152e812b35776?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":558,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/558/kirby","reputation":619,"display_name":"Kirby","accept_rate":52},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1670879794aed7c23742e5b1f759be94?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":1136,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1136/tomd","reputation":2087,"display_name":"TomD"},"score":0,"post_id":3768,"edited":false,"creation_date":1349294730,"comment_id":5729,"body":"You might be interested in the <a href=\"http://web.expasy.org/translate/\" rel=\"nofollow\">exPASy translation tool<\/a> (and loads of other goodies at this site)"}],"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/870fa1db677b2d36510cba57e4d4fd26?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":476,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/476/niallhaslam","reputation":580,"display_name":"niallhaslam"},"score":1,"is_accepted":false,"down_vote_count":0,"last_activity_date":1349282741,"creation_date":1349282741,"body":"<p>EMBOSS has a tool for doing this:\n<a href=\"http://www.ebi.ac.uk/Tools/st/emboss_transeq/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.ebi.ac.uk/Tools/st/emboss_transeq/<\/a><\/p>\n","answer_id":3772,"question_id":3768,"up_vote_count":1},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/VmtoK.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":1320