is indeed made 5'>3', but the template it uses has to run in the opposite direction.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>5\u2019-ATGTACTTCCATCTGGAATAG-3\u2019\n3'-TACATGAAGGTAGACCTTATC-5' template strand\n\n\n5'-AUGUACUUCCAUCUGGAAUAG-3\u2019 mRNA transcript\n3'-TACATGAAGGTAGACCTTATC-5' template strand (read from left to right by the polymerase)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>and the sequence of the protein is MetTyr...etc<\/p>\n","answer_id":3776,"question_id":3768,"up_vote_count":4,"last_edit_date":1349287372}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/3768/translate-dna-to-protein","last_activity_date":1349287372,"creation_date":1349281630,"answer_count":2,"title":"Translate DNA to Protein","body":"<p>Assuming the sequence shown is read left to right, what is the sequence of the protein produced? <\/p>\n\n<p>sequence: 5\u2019-ATGTACTTCCATCTGGAATAG-3\u2019<\/p>\n\n<p>MY ATTEMPT: I know RNA is synthesized 5 to 3.  This is throwing me off because if we read the above sequence from left to right then we are going to synthesize 3 to 5.  If I ignore this for now, I get an mRNA of 3'-UACAUGAAGGUAGACCUUAUC-5'  from this i could easily get the protein looking at a mRNA to protein chart.  Is this correct?<\/p>\n","question_id":3768,"tags":["dna","homework","rna","translation"],"score":2,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":462,"up_vote_count":2},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/7974275b33c1c13d775152e812b35776?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":558,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/558/kirby","reputation":619,"display_name":"Kirby","accept_rate":52},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/5cff3e84bcedd40163c74d33b827ac7c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":307,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/307/lancelafontaine","reputation":3814,"display_name":"LanceLafontaine","accept_rate":47},"score":0,"post_id":3770,"edited":false,"creation_date":1349282946